Installation:

All the interfaces and system files of this directory can be added to the 
TinyOS tree with the install.sh script. First, execution permission needs to
be added to the script with the command

chmod +x intall.sh

If this directory was download in /opt/tinyos-2.x-contrib/ then the script
can be simply launched with:

./install.sh

All the interfaces will be copied in the tree. If this directory was downloaded
somewhere else, the install.sh script needs to be modified. In the first line, the
variable TOSCONTRIB must be changed to the path where this contribution was
downloaded.

Uninstallation:

All the interfaces and system files of this directory can be removed 
from the TinyOS tree with the uninstall.sh script. The usage of this script is
the same as the previous one.
